<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880617-0051 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Ames Department Stores Inc. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> ADD </CO><TEXT>   Ames Department Stores Inc. told shareholders at its annual meeting that its long-term goal is to achieve a pretax profit margin of 5% of sales.    The Rocky Hill, Conn.-based discount department store chain said its pretax margin for the year ended Jan. 31, 1988 was 2.8% on sales of $2.1 billion.    The company said it will concentrate on reducing inventory shrinkage, automation, cost-efficient distribution and higher sales per square foot to reach its goal. </TEXT></DOC>